{"id":20478, "kind":"Bug", "createdAt":"2013-01-15T20:00:49.702515-08:00", "status":"Closed", "title":"raw JSON or XML queries", "category":"MarkLogic Java API", "severity":"Major", "priority":{"level":"5", "title":""}, "submittedBy":{"username":"ehennum", "name":"Erik Hennum", "email":"erik.hennum@marklogic.com"}, "assignTo":{"username":"nobody", "name":"nobody nobody", "email":"nobody@marklogic.com"}, "description":"A Java developer can specify a query definition only as string search or by building\r\na StructuredQueryDefinition with StructuredQueryBuilder.\r\n\r\nTo let the Java developer supply a query definition as raw JSON or XML in any representation,\r\na factory method of QueryManager should return a subordinate interface of QueryDefinition\r\nthat has a setter / getter / fluent for a structured write handle.\r\n\r\n(Note that this work also provide the basis for query-by-example in 7.0) ", "samplequery":"", "sampledata":"", "version":"6.0-nightly", "tofixin":"6.0-3", "fixedin":"6.0-3", "platform":"all", "memory":"", "processors":"", "note":"", "subscribers":[{"username":"ehennum", "name":"Erik Hennum", "email":"erik.hennum@marklogic.com"}, {"username":"ayuwono", "name":"Aries Yuwono", "email":"ayuwono@marklogic.com"}], "attachments":[], "relationships":[{"type":"", "to":""}], "clones":[], "cloneOf":"", "support":{"headline":"Support for raw JSON and XML search requests (including combined queries and options) in the Java API", "supportDescription":"In Java, a query could only be specified by using StructuredQueryBuilder to build a StructuredQueryDefinition object.  In addition, the  query options had to be persisted by name in each request.\r\n\r\nNow,  the subinterfaces of RawQueryDefinition can be used to send a structured query in JSON or XML format. In addition, the structured query can be a combined query that contains the definition of both the query and options.\r\n \r\n", "publishStatus":"Publish", "tickets":[], "customerImpact":{"level":"N/A", "t